{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018t8ixY2dYbmoxgV797YRYx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n- 3 existing nodes: `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, `es-cluster-2`, all with `tier: hot`\n- `app-data` index has 3 primary + 3 replica shards = 6 total, currently healthy (green)\n- The existing cluster uses `node.attr.tier: hot`\n\nMy plan:\n1. Create a new ConfigMap `es-config-warm` with `node.attr.tier: warm`, data-only role, and the correct seed hosts (including the warm nodes)\n2. Set up a headless service and StatefulSet for the warm tier with 2 replicas\n3. Once the warm nodes join the cluster, I'll update the `app-data` index routing policy to move shards to the warm tier—but I need to think through the shard distribution carefully since I have 6 total shards and only 2 warm nodes available.\n\nLooking at the verification requirements, some shards just need to be present on the new nodes, not all of them, so I should use `include.tier: warm` rather than `require` to allow shards to exist on both hot and warm nodes while maintaining cluster health. I need to decide between `include` and `require` for the tier constraint. `include` would allow shards on warm nodes or nodes without the attribute, while `require` forces them exclusively to warm nodes. Since the verification needs to confirm shards are on the new nodes, `require.tier: warm` is the more definitive choice—it guarantees all shards move off the original three nodes. Now I'm thinking through how to configure those new nodes. Finishing the ConfigMap with the remaining seed hosts and initial master nodes, then I'll create the headless service for the warm StatefulSet and set up the StatefulSet itself with 2 replicas. After that, I need to wait for the nodes to join and apply the routing allocation rule to move the `app-data` index to the warm tier. For the headless service, I'm thinking through whether I need a separate one or if I can reuse the existing cluster service.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":515,"cache_read_input_tokens":37467,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":515},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"23d15f3e-77f0-4961-be94-59e5c24bbeaf","uuid":"15023040-f34e-4073-92fc-be8211f2e27a","request_id":"req_011CbyBTQDLziA7ttuMkMyma"}
